data.enText: to say that sth will happen in the future
a reliable method of predicting earthquakes

data.chText: 谁也无法预料结果如何。
预知未来的事是不可能的。
data.enText: It is impossible to predict what will happen.

data.chText: 她预言选举结果将很接近。
data.enText: She predicted (that) the election result would be close.

data.chText: 据预报，通货膨胀率将继续下降。
data.enText: It was predicted that inflation would continue to fall.

data.chText: 预料审讯将持续数月之久。

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+带to的不定式

data.enText: The trial is predicted to last for months.

data.text: This pattern is only used in the passive.
此句型仅用于被动语态。

simple_means.memory_skill: pre 前；预先 + dict 说；断言 → 预言；预告

ex.chText: 一位女巫预言这个女孩将和王子幸福地生活在一起。
ex.enText: A witch foretold that the girl would live happily ever after with a prince.

synonyms.bx: 尤指用特殊的魔力预言某事会发生。

ex.enText: The increase was 3% slower than predicted.

ex.chText: 他预言该执政党将在大选中获得巨大的票数优势。
ex.enText: He predicted that the ruling party would win a huge majority in the election.

synonyms.bx: 指在某事尚未发生的时候就认为某事会发生。

example: Call the outcome of an election

value.def: If you predict an event, you say that it will happen.

example.ex: The latest opinion polls are predicting a very close contest...
example.tran: 最近的民意测验预测竞争将会非常激烈。

example.ex: He predicted that my hair would grow back 'in no time'...
example.tran: 他预言我的头发“一眨眼”就会长回来。

example.ex: It's hard to predict how a jury will react...
example.tran: 很难预测陪审团将会作出何种反应。

example.ex: 'The war will continue another two or three years,' he predicted.
example.tran: “这场战争还会再持续两三年的时间，”他预测道。
